, "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"The main character of Metaphor ReFantazio sits on a golden circle\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\" Image: Studio Zero/Atlus via Polygon\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/10/metaphor_refantazio_beginners_guide_thumbnail_3.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\"><em><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/game/metaphor-refantazio/444905\">Metaphor: ReFantazio</a></em> is a fantastic Persona-like romp through the fantasy genre. But the sheer scale of what\u2019s on offer, combined with the limited number of in-game days to get everything done, means that if you want to do everything in one playthrough, you\u2019re going to need to be efficient.\u00a0</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">From making friends to cooking, cleaning, and crawling dungeons, there\u2019s no shortage of things to do in your quest against the evil ", "id": 1303887, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/metaphor-refantazio-guides/463158/beginners-tips-tricks", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "13 beginner\u2019s tips to know before starting Metaphor: ReFantazio", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-11T00:01:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"The main character of Metaphor ReFantazio reads a book on how long to beat the game\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"Image: Studio Zero/Atlus via Polygon\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/10/metaphor-refantazio-how-long-to-beat.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\"><em><em><em><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/game/metaphor-refantazio/444905\">Metaphor: ReFantazio</a></em></em></em> is from the creators behind <em>Persona 3</em>, <em>4</em> and <em>5</em>. Given those Japanese high school RPGs were all epic affairs, you might be wondering how long it takes to beat this new original fantasy RPG, which shares a similar structure and other gameplay elements. The answer is that it is a pretty long game, although not quite as long as <em>Persona 5</em>, given its calendar timeline covering the st", "id": 1303890, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/metaphor-refantazio-guides/463760/how-long-to-beat-game-length-hours", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "How long does it take to beat Metaphor: ReFantazio?", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-11T00:01:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"The main character of Metaphor ReFantazio wears a crown in the true ending\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"Image: Studio Zero/Atlus via Polygon\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/10/metaphor-refantazio-true-ending.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">There are four <strong>endings</strong> in <em><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/game/metaphor-refantazio/444905\">Metaphor: ReFantazio</a></em> \u2014 parts of the game that technically conclude with a credits scroll. There is, however, <strong>just one real ending</strong> if you wish to complete the story; the other three are bad endings that will cut your journey short.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">There are no trophies or achievements for seeing the bad endings, but it will also not affect your progress in the game, so you might still be", "id": 1303891, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/metaphor-refantazio-guides/463816/endings-all-how-to-get-true", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "How to get all endings in Metaphor: ReFantazio", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-11T00:01:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"The main character of Metaphor ReFantazio engages in debate for Eloquence\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\" Image: Studio Zero/Atlus via Polygon\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/10/metaphor_-refantazio_eloquence_thumbnail_1.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\"><strong>Eloquence</strong> is one of five Royal Virtues in <em><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/game/metaphor-refantazio/444905\">Metaphor: ReFantazio</a></em>. It\u2019s also the hardest to come by (compared to Courage, Wisdom, Tolerance, and Imagination) because opportunities to do so are relatively limited.&nbsp;But not impossible!</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">In this <em>Metaphor: ReFantazio</em> guide, we\u2019ll show you <strong>how to raise Eloquence</strong>, and explain what you get for the effort.</p>\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-sep", "id": 1303888, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/metaphor-refantazio-guides/463373/eloquence-how-to-increase-raise-level-up", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "How to increase Eloquence in Metaphor: ReFantazio", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-11T00:01:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"The main character of Metaphor ReFantazio stands on an airboat with many followers\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\" Image: Studio Zero/Atlus via Polygon\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/10/metaphor-followers-on-gauntlet-runner.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Every monarch needs their supporters, and in<em> <em><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/game/metaphor-refantazio/444905\">Metaphor: ReFantazio</a></em></em>, your Followers are your friends, your comrades, and the most important mechanic in the game.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Followers are <em>Metaphor</em>&#8216;s equivalent of Social Links or Confidants from the Persona games. If you&#8217;ve played those games, you&#8217;ll pick up on how this system works pretty quickly. The loop is simple: gain Followers, improve yo", "id": 1303889, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/metaphor-refantazio-guides/463408/followers-all-list-how-to-unlock", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "How to unlock all Followers in Metaphor: ReFantazio", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-11T00:01:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"Key art showing archetypes in Metaphor ReFantazio\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"Image: Studio Zero/Atlus via Polygon\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/10/metaphor-refantazio-unlock-all-archetypes.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\"><strong>Archetypes</strong> are the class system in in <em><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/game/metaphor-refantazio/444905\">Metaphor: ReFantazio</a></em>, with each one determining the skills an abilities available to you. Over the course of the game, you can invest in them more deeply to grow their power and expand their skillsets as you upgrade them.\u00a0</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Each Archetype revolves around a general playstyle or traditional RPG \u201cjob,\u201d and as you progress, you will slowly unlock all 40+ of them throughout your journey across th", "id": 1303892, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/metaphor-refantazio-guides/463846/archetypes-all-list-how-to-unlock-jobs-classes", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "How to unlock Archetypes in Metaphor: ReFantazio", "vote": 0}]